The architects have understood that the offices need childcare
The administrative building Avriopoint in Brno is the headquarters of the company Arch.Design.
No one would say that it hides also inside a small nursery with own such facilities: walls of colors, creative furniture and even a miniature in the outdoor terrace Park.
Since October of last year, can go to the children of employees of Arch.Design.
The company's architectural projects Arch.Design, whose study came out many well-known buildings in Brno, thought from the first sketches of the Avriopoint building to include a space for your miniguardería.
In the company they work around 90 people, mainly in the age of the baby boom and wanted to allow that the architects and draughtsmen could return soon to work after motherhood.
Together with the possibility to enjoy a half day, day care is one of the benefits offered by Arch.Design to their workers in the framework of its social agenda.
Builders and architects in this way have the possibility of combining a profession demanding with the care of children.
The miniguardería was an idea of the own employees of Arch.Designu and, with the support of the direction, managed to obtain funding from the European Union and the Ministry of labour and Social Affairs.
The miniguardería of the company is financed by the European Social Fund within the framework of the operational programme human resources and employment, as well as the State budget of the Czech Republic.
Granted funding (an endowment of more than 2.8 million Czech Crowns) they could buy the equipment and, after two years, hiring qualified staff and services.
When it runs out of funding (two years), the Arch.Design company has an obligation to keep running the miniguardería with their own funds for three years.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and in the filing of the application of funding helped the Economy Rating company.
The care of children is in the hands of qualified personnel; In addition, are present throughout the day for their care a nurse and a teacher of the Ministry of education. The nursery currently welcomes children without age limit, although most of them have less than three years.
Given that it's a "miniguardería," only it can accommodate simultaneously to a maximum of five children, although with the shifts they come more during the day.
The operation of the kindergarten is flexible to adapt to the needs of parents and children of all workers have the right to use the nursery, regardless of hierarchy within the company.
Although this is a teaching and individual care, the content of the programme of the miniguardería are comparable to regular pre-school education programme.
Her children not only play, but they also receive a quality education: from the basic learning until the preparation for the school, taught to English.
The class not only has toys and games table, but also a computer for children.
The presence of young children in the company create a friendly and positive atmosphere.
Parents can go to see their children at any time and avoid the stress of late collect children from school when you are away from their place of work.
Thus, parents are more productive while working.
It is not surprising that this will generate in a natural way a relationship of loyalty between the worker and his employer.
Thus, Arch.Design is situated between the companies sign that they offer a great advantage for the admission of new workers: supporting the family and, ultimately, this programme strengthened the marketing staff.
