US changes rules for visa
People should go to the centers of service for Visa applicants before his interview at the Consular section; the cost will be less and as well as the waiting time.
The procedure to process a visa at the Embassy of United States and consulates will change starting on January 10, 2011.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants must attend service centres for Visa applicants (ASC) before his interview at the Consular section.
The staff of the ASC will take the biometric information of the applicant, which will be reviewed by the Consular section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for applicants, among which are:
The total cost of processing the visa will be less, will no longer be necessary to make a payment to make the appointment, another payment for processing the visa application and another messaging service deliver the document.
The candidate will only be a lump sum that will cover all three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in case of visa request (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for visas of traders and investors.
Persons wishing to renew their visa will not have to attend an interview with the Consular Officer, they will only go to the nearest ASC where they will present their papers and shall take you your fingerprints.
Because the biometric information will be taken at the ASC, applicants that require a second date to be interviewed at the Consular section, will remain in this less time than in the past.
Also, who apply for visa at the Consulate in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo not already paid the extra $26 service fee.
For additional information about the new procedure to apply for a visa, visit the following page http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
